                        <TextBlock Style="{StaticResource HelpH2}">Core Concepts</TextBlock>

                        <TextBlock Style="{StaticResource HelpH3}">BaseNode</TextBlock>
                        <TextBlock Style="{StaticResource HelpBody}">Every node inherits from BaseNode. It defines Setup() (ports and properties) and Process() (main logic). Nodes have typed input/output ports and configurable properties.</TextBlock>

                        <TextBlock Style="{StaticResource HelpH3}">NodeGraph</TextBlock>
                        <TextBlock Style="{StaticResource HelpBody}">The graph container manages nodes and connections. It enforces connection rules (type compatibility, cycle prevention), tracks dirty state, and provides thread-safe snapshots for execution.</TextBlock>

                        <TextBlock Style="{StaticResource HelpH3}">GraphExecutor</TextBlock>
                        <TextBlock Style="{StaticResource HelpBody}">The execution engine. Uses Kahn's algorithm for topological sorting. Supports three modes: single-shot, continuous streaming (camera), and runtime (event-driven, dirty-node-only). Handles loop execution (For, While, ForEach) with nested loop support.</TextBlock>

                        <TextBlock Style="{StaticResource HelpH3}">Data Flow</TextBlock>
                        <TextBlock Style="{StaticResource HelpBody}">Pull-based data flow. InputPort.GetValue() follows the connection to the source OutputPort. Nodes are executed in topological order. Only dirty nodes are re-executed in runtime mode (incremental execution).</TextBlock>

                        <TextBlock Style="{StaticResource HelpH3}">FunctionNode</TextBlock>
                        <TextBlock Style="{StaticResource HelpBody}">Loads a saved project (.mvxp) as a reusable sub-graph. SubGraphAnalyzer identifies boundary ports: source nodes (in-degree 0) become inputs, sink nodes (out-degree 0) become outputs. Executes the sub-graph internally with its own GraphExecutor.</TextBlock>

